🚀 STEP 1: Install Docker on EC2

Connect to your EC2 and run:

sudo apt update
sudo apt install docker.io -y

Start Docker:

sudo systemctl start docker

Enable auto-start:

sudo systemctl enable docker
🔐 STEP 2: Run Docker Without sudo (Important)
sudo usermod -aG docker ubuntu

👉 Then logout & reconnect:

exit
ssh -i your-key.pem ubuntu@YOUR_EC2_IP
🧪 STEP 3: Test Docker
docker run hello-world

👉 If it prints success → Docker is working ✅

📁 STEP 4: Go to Your Project
cd website-monitor

docker run hello-world

👉 If it prints success → Docker is working ✅

📁 STEP 4: Go to Your Project
cd website-monitor
🧱 STEP 5: Create Dockerfile
nano Dockerfile
STEP 6: Build Docker Image
docker build -t website-monitor .
▶️ STEP 7: Run Container
docker run -d --name monitor-container website-monitor
🔍 STEP 8: Check Running Container
docker ps
📊 STEP 9: Check Logs
docker logs monitor-container

Or inside container:

docker exec -it monitor-container bash
cat /app/log.txt
🛑 STOP / REMOVE CONTAINER
docker stop monitor-container
docker rm monitor-container


--cron job--
✅ STEP 1: Install Cron

Run this:

sudo apt update
sudo apt install cron -y
▶️ STEP 2: Start Cron Service
sudo systemctl start cron

Enable it to start automatically:

sudo systemctl enable cron
🔍 STEP 3: Verify Installation
crontab -l

👉 If you see:

no crontab for ubuntu

✔️ That means it’s working

📝 STEP 4: Add Your Cron Job
crontab -e

Add this line:

*/2 * * * * /bin/bash /home/ubuntu/website-monitor/monitor.sh >> /home/ubuntu/website-monitor/cron.log 2>&1
💾 Save
Press CTRL + X
Press Y
Press Enter